It is a living memorial of one who long served and honored the civil-engineering profession, and who assiduously and patiently devoted the latter part of his life to the educa- tion of the striving student-- the late Prof. Gillespie. The Club is essentially engineering, its proceedings being in the interest of the pro- fession, and its members comprising those \vho are taking the engineering course.
